task.summary: Update toolboxes.Initialization Put hard-coded parameters into class attributes so that they can be accessed and modified with easy. Unify random number generation with uniform distribution with low and high. All member functions are modified accordingly. randomly_generate_sparse_A_matrix has all functionalities of randomly_generate_A_matrix, so remove randomly_generate_A_matrix and rename randomly_generate_sparse_A_matrix as randomly_generate_A_matrix

# package structure rearrangement and add parameter graph THE MOST IMPORTANT THING IS KEEPING INTEGRALTITY AND CONSISTENCE OF DATA UNIT. Class DataUnit should have a hidden dictionary recording all the parameters and scanned data. It should only be written by DataUnit's methods to keep integrality and consistence but should be read easily. Data should be put in to levels. If one parameter uses other parameters on at most n level, it in at n+1 level. Ideally, parameters should be specified only from higher level to lower level and it should be pretty easy to generate lower level parameters randomly with higher level parameters. In the fully random case, only level 0 parameters are necessary to be set. Whenever one wants to set a parameter, DataUnit should check its consistence with existing parameters. But it may be too complex and time consuming. Now, use it as a guide line rather than strict requirement. Build parameter level relationship graph. Previous Project, Study, Scanner structure are not necessary so are not used.
ParameterGraph and ParameterGraph.generate_gv_file are added. They plot parameter graph with dot tool to show dependency between parameters. Nicely, the parameter level are very easy to read from the graph, so it's no longer needed to be tracked manually.
Update ParameterGraph.generate_gv_file level lables are added and parameters at the same level are put into the same rank
DataUnit inherits from Initialization and add DataUnit.abstract_flag

Use category mechanism for secured parameter assignment. Base on prerequisites, put parameters in to 3 categories. Category one: no prerequisites, should be assigned value directly Category two: with prerequisite and has if_random_ flag in prerequisites, one needs to check flag before assign Category three: with prerequisite and has no flag, should not be assigned directly, its value should be derived by its prerequisites.
